The paper presents a new Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) architecture for semantic image segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the design of the network and its training process, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The use of convolutional neural networks is a common technique in neural networks, which could also make cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with semantic image segmentation, which is a task related to natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
